data.title: Photos, facts, and identification tips
data.meta_description: Learn about New England ducks, geese and swans (family: Anatidae). Find photos, facts, sounds, and identification tips for these birds.
data.text:
Learn interesting facts about New England ducks, geese, and waterfowl.

Find photos, sounds, range information and identification tips for each bird.

Anatidae is a family of small to very large-sized birds which are distributed world-wide, including all continents except Antarctica. Well adapted for swimming, they are found in a wide variety of aquatic habitats, including lakes, ponds, and marshes as well as the moving water of streams and rivers.
